# Tethered Photography via Wireless LAN

Connect to a wireless LAN to use a computer on the network for tethered photography.

1. Select **CREATE/EDIT CONNECTION SETTING > CREATE USING WIZARD** in the network/USB setting menu and choose **TETHERED SHOOTING**.

   !Tether Shooting Menu

2. Select **CREATE NEW**.

   !Create New Option

   > ðŸ’¡ **Tip:**  
   > Choose **SELECT FROM LIST** to select from a list of existing connection setting profiles.

3. Press **MENU/OK** when prompted.

   !Select Comm Setting

4. Select **WIRELESS LAN**.

   !Wireless LAN Option

5. Select **CREATE NEW** to create a new communication setting profile.

   !Comm Setting Profile

   > ðŸ’¡ **Tip:**  
   > You can also select or edit existing profiles.
